      <hr style="width:50px;border:5px solid red" class="w3-round">
      <p>Best to begin when your puppy is still young. Somewhere between 10 weeks and 3 months old.</p>
      <p>These first few months of introducing your pet into it’s home and broader environment is critical to establish confidence, trust and structure.</p>
      <p>The training will familiarise the owner and pet with diverse circumstances and interactions that will pop-up in daily life.</p>
      <p>These sessions are invaluable to form a stimulating and loving bond between the puppy and humans for life.</p>
  </div>

